title: Roundup: Morris gets big volleyball win at Yorkville
text:
Roundup: Morris gets big volleyball win at Yorkville Published: Tuesday, Oct. 20, 2015 9:27 p.m. CDT By: STAFF REPORTS 
YORKVILLE – Last week, the Morris volleyball team lost a tough, three-game decision to Kaneland on senior night. 
On Tuesday, the Redskins had a chance to make Northern Illinois Big 12 East rival Yorkville suffer the same fate. 
Morris didn’t even take three games, as the Redskins beat Yorkville, 25-17, 25-15. 
“It was senior night for them and the girls came in with a great momentum,” Morris coach Taylor Lafond said. “They wanted to defend themselves from when we lost to them at home. It was a great match that we had control over for the entire way.” 
Kaylin Korte had 21 kills, nine digs and one block for Morris (13-16-2, 3-4). Janelle Brehm had six kills, two digs, three aces and four blocks. Addison Polite had 12 assists, three digs and an ace, while Ashley Hood had 12 assists, one dig and an ace, and Veronica Johnson had two kills and two blocks. 
Morris won the sophomore match, 16-25, 28-26, 25-23, while the freshman A team lost, 19-25, 25-15, 25-12, and the B team lost, 25-19, 25-10. 
Newark 25-25, IMSA 15-20: Maddie Friestad had eight kills to lead Newark (22-5), while Kelsea Zitt had six kills and six digs. Marissa Friestad collected 15 assists, with Megan DeClementi adding 11 digs and Nikki Kala five kills.
